}
,"name": "Molten Chocolate Cake"
,"aggregateRating": {
"@type": "AggregateRating",
"ratingValue": "4.6",
"ratingCount": "73"
}
,"nutrition": {
"@type": "NutritionInformation"
,"calories": "624 kcal"
,"carbohydrateContent": "28 g"
,"cholesterolContent": "294 mg"
,"fiberContent": "7 g"
,"proteinContent": "14 g"
,"saturatedFatContent": "30 g"
,"sodiumContent": "165 mg"
,"sugarContent": "13 g"
,"fatContent": "51 g"
,"unsaturatedFatContent": "0 g"
}
, "recipeCategory": ["Dessert"]
,"recipeCuisine": ["American"]
,"recipeIngredient": [
"1 stick (4 ounces) unsalted butter",
"2 tablespoons all-purpose flour",
"6 ounces bittersweet chocolate, preferably Valrhona",
"2 eggs",
"2 egg yolks",
"1/4 cup sugar",
"Pinch of salt" ]
,"recipeInstructions": [
{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.foodandwine.com/thmb/3uhpCgk7lKk4Afp2vsTNJRQG6_8=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/FAW-recipes-molten-chocolate-cakes-ingredients-7d92cea7995a43da8b0e14cf5258f0e7.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Gather the ingredients."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.foodandwine.com/thmb/WCOQ035qgT2hGTPqzapKrvy8swQ=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/FAW-recipes-molten-chocolate-cakes-step-01-962dc901317e466c9ae12fcbfab644a2.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Preheat oven to 450°F. Butter and lightly flour four 6-ounce ramekins. Tap out excess flour. Set the ramekins on a baking sheet."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.foodandwine.com/thmb/kfOvm26bQw7N8OB2x6SK0Gv6xS4=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/FAW-recipes-molten-chocolate-cakes-step-02-247a4d39e28345da8eead6a616a8a28b.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Fill a medium saucepan with water to a depth of 1 inch; bring to a boil over medium-high and reduce heat to medium-low to maintain a simmer. Combine chocolate and butter in a medium-size heatproof bowl and set bowl over simmering water in pan, making sure bottom of bowl doesn’t touch water. Cook over medium-low, stirring occasionally and adjusting heat as needed to maintain a simmer, until chocolate mixture is melted and smooth, 16 to 20 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.foodandwine.com/thmb/RrkXZGUDKKVzM4Ezdm7_0lIB6ko=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/FAW-recipes-molten-chocolate-cakes-step-03-4a7e7263f35643bd9935348db16c0f70.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Beat eggs, egg yolks, sugar, and salt in a medium bowl with an electric mixer fitted with the whisk attachment on high speed until thickened and pale, 2 to 3 minutes"
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.foodandwine.com/thmb/37DGbtjpCWLvZymVbi_ILQSACQc=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/FAW-recipes-molten-chocolate-cakes-step-04-1db99f2a09c44893b353a05c5ae48657.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Whisk melted chocolate until smooth."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.foodandwine.com/thmb/-n2llxD30pOCq-ANeBrGOGwfe2I=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/FAW-recipes-molten-chocolate-cakes-step-05-966aa66f719e4afab6cec86bddc75091.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Quickly fold melted chocolate mixture and flour into egg mixture in bowl until well combined and no streaks remain."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.foodandwine.com/thmb/TmnELOws7IFRM9TwXXgqRmWJ4oM=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/FAW-recipes-molten-chocolate-cakes-step-06-27e09953e958425d8502556350163d81.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Spoon batter into prepared ramekins (about 1/2 cup per ramekin) and smooth the top using a small offset spatula if needed. Place baking sheet with ramekins in the preheated oven; bake until tops of cakes are just set and edges spring back when touched but centers still feel soft, about 9 to 12 minutes."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"image": [
{
"@type": "ImageObject",
"url": "https://www.foodandwine.com/thmb/XdFd-DvTtouryLCjeCqwhfmmK-A=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/molten-chocolate-cake-FT-RECIPE0220-0a33d7d0ab0c45588f7bfe742d33a9bc.jpg"
}
]
,"text": "Remove cakes from oven and let cool in ramekins on baking sheet for 1 minute. Working with one ramekin at a time, cover ramekin with an inverted dessert plate. Carefully turn over and let stand 10 seconds before lifting the ramekin to unmold cake. Repeat unmolding procedure with remaining cakes. Serve immediately."
} ]
,"recipeYield": "4"
,"totalTime": "PT35M"
,"review": [
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "EagerSpoon1435"
}
,
"reviewBody": "Okay, you haters... Here's what I did, and it worked out PERFECTLY. First off, I took the advice of someone down the chain, and refrigerated the batter, thus guaranteeing molten centers. When you spoon into the ramekins, it will be thick as cold Jell-O Pudding Cups. Fret not, just do your best to spoon into the ramekins, filling to the interior shoulder. NOTE that mine are 8oz, so they had to cook longer. I tested three different cakes: 12, 15 and 17 minutes, and the 17m cook time worked perfectly – again, batter straight from the fridge each time! A few other related notes... I added a capful of vanilla (because why not?), and I used Cup4Cup GF flour. (NOTE: I have used C4C extensively alongside regular flour, and it doesn't materially change cook times.) I beat the egg/sugar mixture on high for a solid 3 minutes... I used Guittard Semi-Sweet Chocolate Chips... cooked in a Wolf oven (confirmed 450 with an oven thermometer)... and I let cakes cool for 3 mins instead of the prescribed 1 min before inverting onto a plate. Lastly, it says to \"serve immediately\". Sure, but if you try actually eating it immediately, you'll likely have 3rd degree burns in your mouth. Test before devouring – which you will do, because it was delicious!"
},
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Jillian Rodrigues de Miranda"
},
"reviewBody": "I have made this at least 10 times and never a fail. Hubby nearly requires it for special occasions. A real staple for special dinners in our home.",
"datePublished": "2025-06-13T13:43:51.169Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Food & Wine Member"
},
"reviewBody": "",
"datePublished": "2025-04-28T03:43:58.825Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "carissap"
},
"reviewBody": "I think it’s sheer perfection for a chocolate lava cake recipe!!",
"datePublished": "2025-04-22T10:39:41.960Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Food & Wine Member"
},
"reviewBody": "I’m no cook. But this was easy and to my surprise turned out great! Followed directions as listed but listened to the advice of refrigerating first and only cooked for 9 minutes. Will definitely make again!",
"datePublished": "2025-02-17T22:23:33.317Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Food & Wine Member"
},
"reviewBody": "We made our first test recipe yesterday. We followed the recipe to a tee, and I must say it is so good! We made a second recipe earlier today and will take them to a Superbowl party this evening. I think it will be a real hit. So chocolatey. Five Stars!",
"datePublished": "2025-02-09T21:16:31.446Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "Food & Wine Member"
},
"reviewBody": "I loved this recipe! I made it for my boyfriend and his friends and they loved it! I cooked it for about 10-11 minutes, and the outside was cooked with the perfect gooey centre. I kept an eye on it after 9 minutes to ensure I did not overcook it. I don't know what everyone is complaining about, I found it amazing when I made it. Just follow the recipe closely, and it works perfectly.",
"datePublished": "2025-02-09T03:19:14.535Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "kellmell"
},
"reviewBody": "I never, ever, write reviews. But I had to defend this recipe. I have been using it FOR YEARS for an easy, impressive go-to…but only with one method - MAKE AHEAD!!! Not only will you have an easy dessert, but the middle becomes truly molten. I take them out of fridge 30 minutes before baking for 12 minutes and they never fail to give me perfect molten perfection. I don’t even bother taking them out of the ramekins…just heap a scoop of ice cream on top and serve it on a salad plate (because obviously the ramekins are hot). There will be naysayers, I know, but don’t knock it til you try it.",
"datePublished": "2025-02-06T22:15:45.322Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "FantasticEspresso5650"
},
"reviewBody": "Came out great for me. Followed advice and refrigerated the batter. I only have 120ml (4oz) ramekins and my air fryer only goes up to 205ºC (401ºF). I put 2 in at a time for 7 minutes, and they came out perfect. Might go for 6 minutes next time for a bit of an extra gooey centre. I let them sit for 2–3 minutes inverted on the plate before removing the ramekin and serving.",
"datePublished": "2025-01-26T08:13:49.736Z"
}
,
{
"@type": "Review",
"reviewRating": {
"@type": "Rating",
"ratingValue": "5"
},
"author": {
"@type": "Person",
"name": "cbnbemis"
},
"reviewBody": "Amazing and easier than I expected. My son used his air fryer and adjusted the time to about 9 minutes. We even made a couple with Splenda for baking instead of sugar that came out very good. Those only took about 7-8 minutes to cook in the air fryer. This is definitely a keeper recipe!",
"datePublished": "2024-11-05T20:27:55.177Z"
}
]
