, "about": [
{
"@type": "FAQPage",
"mainEntity": [
{
"@type": "Question",
"name": "How can you tell if molten lava cake is done?",
"acceptedAnswer": {
"@type": "Answer",
"text": "<p>The best way to tell if molten chocolate lava cake is done is by analyzing its surface. Once the tops of the cakes are just set and have a light spring when poked, the cake should be fully cooked. (The center should still have a slight jiggle.) However, a toothpick can help determine the cake&#39;s doneness with greater certainty; it should come out clean when inserted in the outer edges of the cake but should leave some residue from the batter when inserted in the center.<\/p>"
}
}
,
{
"@type": "Question",
"name": "How long do you heat up lava cake?",
"acceptedAnswer": {
"@type": "Answer",
"text": "<p>Lava cake can be reheated after being refrigerated or frozen. If it hasn&#39;t been thawed, reheat it in a 400ºF oven for roughly 15 minutes. If it&#39;s coming from the refrigerator, nine minutes in a 350ºF oven should do the trick.<\/p>"
}
}
]
